  "texts": [
    "It reflects the ratio of correct predictions to the total predictions made.",
    "SEN represents the proportion of tests that accurately detect true instances of disease, essentially capturing the true positive rate.",
    "On the other hand, SPE denotes the proportion of tests that accurately identify non-diseased individuals, constituting the true negative rate.",
    "PRE represents the proportion of samples with a positive prediction that is actually positive.",
    "F1-score is a weighted average of PRE and Recall."
